import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['population'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of engineers and the population?')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    engineers_by_state = data.groupby('state')['engineers'].sum().reset_index()
    engineers_by_state = engineers_by_state.sort_values(by='engineers', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(engineers_by_state['state'], engineers_by_state['engineers'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Year').sum()
    plt.plot(data.index, data['Hurricanes'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hurricanes across the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
